Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.30,0:00:03.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Victory! Honesty! The shocking evidence!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.18,0:00:04.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The impulse takes it to the limit!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.97,0:00:06.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ueto Aya-san shares the spotlight for the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.47,0:00:09.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Due to a case, Shinichi's promise comes up once again!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.56,0:00:10.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perceiving the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.94,0:00:12.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A child with the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.60,0:00:14.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.78,0:01:44.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.61,0:01:46.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, Suba-kun and Kobayashi-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.41,0:01:47.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't believe it!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.59,0:01:49.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.01,0:01:49.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yuki!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.87,0:01:52.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The tennis club's...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.75,0:01:53.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kitada-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.58,0:01:55.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yuki...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.00,0:01:57.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.92,0:01:58.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kitada!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.84,0:02:00.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kitada-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.72,0:02:06.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kitada...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.44,0:02:15.32,Signs,,0,0,0,,Female High School Detective - Yuki's Casebook
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.32,0:02:19.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\an8\fscy120\fscx120\b1\1c&HC8C2BD&\3c&H3C322F&\bord4\be2\}Oshibana High School
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.94,0:02:21.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The formula of deduction...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.44,0:02:23.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Must be applied to the equation of this mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.61,0:02:24.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The solution is obvious from there.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.98,0:02:56.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As I thought...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.94,0:02:58.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As I thought, Sensei is the culprit!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.12,0:03:14.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is the answer, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.55,0:03:21.55,Signs,,0,0,0,,UETO AYA & SHINICHI\NTHE PROMISE FROM 4 YEARS AGO
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.46,0:03:25.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's a pretty girl like me doing\Nhere on a bright and sunny day...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.92,0:03:29.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dusting things and tiring herself out?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.13,0:03:31.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's that demon, I tell you! That demon!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.14,0:03:35.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't believe she got her daughter-in-law\Nto clean up an empty house.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.68,0:03:37.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your mother-in-law really is a demon! A demon!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.77,0:03:38.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.77,0:03:42.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't bring up "daughter-in-law" or\N"mother in-law" or anything like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.06,0:03:43.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wanted to do this anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.94,0:03:46.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't even ask you to help, Sonoko.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.78,0:03:48.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess that's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.86,0:03:51.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But this really is something, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.66,0:03:54.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The sheer number of books.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.29,0:04:02.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Yami no Danshaku: Night Baron."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.29,0:04:05.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Books by Kudou Yuusaku are all over here, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.55,0:04:12.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Female High School Detective - Yuki's Casebook."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.59,0:04:13.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.10,0:04:16.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They made a TV version of this a while ago, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.76,0:04:17.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, right!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.43,0:04:18.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was a two-hour drama.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.89,0:04:21.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's one of Dad's earlier works.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.64,0:04:23.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I read it now, though, the story seems a bit childish.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.57,0:04:29.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't this Ueto Aya-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.65,0:04:31.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.82,0:04:33.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She had just received her first starring role...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.41,0:04:37.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And visited Shinichi's parents with her\Nmanager when this picture was taken.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.37,0:04:40.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that you mention it, I think I've heard of it before.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.20,0:04:42.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It happened a few years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.00,0:04:44.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was in my first year of junior high,\Nso about four years ago, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.17,0:04:48.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was a really big fan of Aya-chan's back then, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.50,0:04:49.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After Shinichi told me...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.84,0:04:52.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was so excited that I brought along.\Nsomething for her to sign, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.72,0:04:55.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shinichi didn't seem too interested in Aya-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.64,0:04:58.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He just played with his soccer ball by himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.60,0:05:00.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I saw Aya-chan's expression...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.56,0:05:04.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And remember her looking especially serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.35,0:05:08.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Afterwards, I asked Shinichi what they were talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.98,0:05:09.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What did he say?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.11,0:05:10.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.99,0:05:12.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.20,0:05:15.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really, I wonder what was said then...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.41,0:05:16.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shinichi...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.45,0:05:20.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe they were arranging some kind of date?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.25,0:05:24.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sonoko, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.08,0:05:25.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How is that even possible?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.67,0:05:28.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone's at the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.96,0:05:30.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.73,0:05:31.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uhm...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.05,0:05:34.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is Kudou Shinichi-san there?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.34,0:05:34.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.68,0:05:37.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sounds like a young woman...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.51,0:05:39.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sony, Shinichi isn't home right now...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.68,0:05:40.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,May I ask who this is?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.89,0:05:44.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A young woman...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.02,0:05:49.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ueto...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.73,0:05:52.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is Ueto Aya.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.07,0:05:55.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ueto Aya-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.12,0:06:07.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's really her!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.25,0:06:10.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's really Ueto Aya-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.51,0:06:16.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you remember me?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.18,0:06:18.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.30,0:06:19.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're Mouri Ran-san, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.93,0:06:21.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shinichi-san's childhood friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.97,0:06:23.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.48,0:06:25.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is my classmate...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.69,0:06:27.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Suzuki Sonoko-chan here!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.60,0:06:28.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nice to meet you!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.40,0:06:30.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.48,0:06:32.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is Conan-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.44,0:06:33.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Good afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.23,0:06:34.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, good afternoon...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.99,0:06:36.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're embarrassed, aren't you, you little four-eyed brat?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.24,0:06:38.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shut up.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.78,0:06:41.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you know when Shinichi-san will be back?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.16,0:06:42.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know either.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.83,0:06:44.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ever since he started investigating a certain case, he...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.87,0:06:47.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Miss, are you looking for Shinichi-niichan?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.96,0:06:49.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you want him to investigate something for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.08,0:06:51.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.25,0:06:53.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is there a way for me to contact Shinichi-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.80,0:06:55.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About that...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.13,0:06:57.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if you call his cell, most of the\Ntime you have to leave a message.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.13,0:06:59.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I can try calling him for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.05,0:07:01.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry to trouble you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.64,0:07:04.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's useless, given I'm right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.64,0:07:07.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, if you want to have something\Nlooked into, Mouri Kogorou can...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.39,0:07:09.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uncle probably won't be able to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.94,0:07:10.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.86,0:07:13.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He got drunk last night and didn't get up this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.82,0:07:15.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No point getting him, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.53,0:07:17.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just his answering machine again.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.03,0:07:19.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.49,0:07:20.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How frustrating...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.74,0:07:23.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, even if you have to leave a message...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.62,0:07:26.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you tell him about the case in it,\NShinichi-niichan might come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.87,0:07:27.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.96,0:07:30.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it isn't too much trouble, could you tell us about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.96,0:07:36.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next to my apartment building, there's\Nan old woman named Koda Fumie-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.05,0:07:39.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's about 80 years old and lives alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.43,0:07:44.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Grandma and I are on good terms, so I visit\Nher house often while on vacation, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.10,0:07:47.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I went to see her again today...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.77,0:07:48.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Grandma?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.77,0:07:49.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's Aya.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.60,0:07:50.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm coming in now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.15,0:07:53.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Grandma, I came to visit.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.61,0:07:55.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Grandma?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.61,0:08:01.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.07,0:08:02.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where did she go?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.91,0:08:08.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Grandma usually leaves the door unlocked\Nwhenever she goes to buy groceries nearby.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.41,0:08:10.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought today was no different...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.12,0:08:12.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I waited at her house, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.50,0:08:14.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She didn't come home, did she?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.42,0:08:15.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.42,0:08:19.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I grew a little worried and decided to go\Nto the vegetable market to ask around.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.47,0:08:20.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the end...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.55,0:08:23.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, that old woman you're talking about just passed by.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.76,0:08:26.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I asked her where she was\Nheaded, she replied "Beika District."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.01,0:08:28.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Beika District?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.14,0:08:28.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.89,0:08:31.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's all she said before hurrying on her way.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.23,0:08:34.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She definitely looked more flustered than usual.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.31,0:08:36.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm a little worried, myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.77,0:08:40.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then, I called a taxi and got\Nto Beika as quickly as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.78,0:08:43.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I didn't know why Grandma would come here, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.91,0:08:45.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I had no idea where to start.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.12,0:08:49.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At that moment, Shinichi-san's name came to mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.79,0:08:53.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although I only saw him that once, four years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.75,0:08:56.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've heard he became a very active high school detective...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.54,0:08:58.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that he lives around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.00,0:09:00.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that's why you came here to find him?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.92,0:09:01.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.67,0:09:02.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But he and I...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.01,0:09:07.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Never mind that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.31,0:09:12.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Does that old lady know anyone in Beika District?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.77,0:09:14.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.69,0:09:18.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, I should send Shinichi a mail with all this information.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.23,0:09:21.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is there anything else you know about that old lady?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.24,0:09:28.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shinichi-niichan has always said that the\Nmore information you get, the better!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.20,0:09:31.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.20,0:09:32.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What else...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.58,0:09:36.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When Grandma was younger, her\Ndaughter died of some illness.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.67,0:09:37.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Her daughter?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.21,0:09:42.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Half a year ago, I found out about\Nit from one of Grandma's friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.67,0:09:46.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was when Fumie-chan was about 40.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.80,0:09:49.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Her only daughter, A ako-chan, was only 17 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.39,0:09:55.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fumie-chan was an unwed mother,\Nraising Ayako-chan on her own.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.14,0:09:58.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That day, she went to work as usual...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.48,0:10:03.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While she was away, Ayako-chan suddenly became ill.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.69,0:10:07.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the time Fumie-chan came back,\NAyako-chan was already, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.91,0:10:12.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fumie-chan felt guilty for not being able\Nto see Ayako-chan one last time...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.41,0:10:16.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She kept thinking that she caused her daughter's death.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.17,0:10:18.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I never knew about that...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.88,0:10:21.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fumie-chan won't tell anyone about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.75,0:10:23.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that I think about it...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.21,0:10:25.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You really look like Ayako-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.09,0:10:27.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even your name is Aya-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.80,0:10:30.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That must be why she took a special liking to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.47,0:10:32.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm home.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.72,0:10:35.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I bought so much that it's made me late.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.68,0:10:36.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Welcome home.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.89,0:10:38.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't tell anyone what I just said.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.94,0:10:44.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Grandma was always smiling.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.15,0:10:47.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Never in my wildest dreams did I\Nthink that she lived with such pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.86,0:10:51.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,17 years old—that's around our age, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.53,0:10:52.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It must have been hard...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.83,0:10:55.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For that old lady and her daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.58,0:11:00.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I remember correctly, her daughter really loved\Nclassical music—particularly any of Mozart's works.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.00,0:11:04.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is what she just said related to the situation?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.30,0:11:05.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I still don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.59,0:11:08.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe I can look at this another way?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.97,0:11:12.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, when Aya-san entered the living room...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.01,0:11:14.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The TV was already off, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.47,0:11:17.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before Grandma went out, she\Nmay have been watching it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.77,0:11:19.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.19,0:11:21.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I saw that the newspaper on the table was\Nturned to a page with TV listings on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.90,0:11:23.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was the tea cup half empty?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.78,0:11:27.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means the old lady was watching TV...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.28,0:11:29.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And only left the house because\Nsomething came to mind, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.86,0:11:31.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you remember what channel it was on?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.57,0:11:33.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.62,0:11:35.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While I was waiting for Grandma...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.08,0:11:39.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nichiuri TV!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.46,0:11:41.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nichiuri TV...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.88,0:11:43.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nichiuri TV, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.25,0:11:43.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.04,0:11:45.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.05,0:11:48.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just want to look into the types of shows she watches.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.05,0:11:51.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shinichi-niichan doesn't subscribe\Nto any newspapers, does he?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.34,0:11:54.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That must be why you want to call someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.05,0:11:54.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.93,0:11:56.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"No" what?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.18,0:11:58.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can actually do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.69,0:12:03.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't this the show we were talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.15,0:12:06.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's this one!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.40,0:12:08.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Female High School Detective - Yuki's Casebook."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.99,0:12:11.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're airing a rerun of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.07,0:12:11.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.95,0:12:13.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.53,0:12:16.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even the star of the show herself didn't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.74,0:12:17.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.16,0:12:21.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The drama was filmed in Beika District, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.04,0:12:24.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Beika Station, Beika Park...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.08,0:12:25.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the Shitara Shunichi Memorial Hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.42,0:12:28.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's that old western-style house!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.51,0:12:32.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although his wife later turned it into a memorial hall...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.63,0:12:35.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before that, it was the home to a\Npianist that died ten years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.14,0:12:39.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the drama, after Aya-san was\Nknocked unconscious by the criminal...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.02,0:12:41.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was locked in the hall's basement, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.98,0:12:42.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.02,0:12:45.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the exterior there was only filmed as a backdrop.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.44,0:12:47.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The indoor scenes were shot on a set elsewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.11,0:12:48.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.32,0:12:49.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I understand!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.44,0:12:53.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I understand now why that old lady ventured to Beika.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.91,0:12:54.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really, Sonoko?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.99,0:12:56.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.16,0:12:59.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Female high school detective Suzuki Sonoko's deductions...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.67,0:13:05.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are never wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.05,0:13:09.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is she all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.14,0:13:15.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Listen.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.97,0:13:19.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That old lady must have trouble\Ndifferentiating between dramas and reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.81,0:13:22.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.06,0:13:24.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's likely that, once she looked at the\NTV listings in the newspaper...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.22,0:13:27.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\an8}And saw Aya-san's name...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.06,0:13:29.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\an8}She made sure to watch the drama once it began.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.44,0:13:33.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She watched half of it but then fell asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.90,0:13:37.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, by the time she woke up, the\Nsecond half was already airing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.87,0:13:43.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She saw Aya-san be attacked in surprise and end up\Nbeing held in that western-style house's basement.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.21,0:13:46.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The old lady, who had only just woken up...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.33,0:13:48.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perceived the action in the drama as reality, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.38,0:13:51.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Left her home and set out on her own to rescue Aya-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.88,0:13:55.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Afterward, she came straight over to Beika.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.47,0:13:58.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But doesn't that mean the TV had to be on the whole time?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.60,0:14:01.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since the TV was off later...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.39,0:14:04.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She must have recognized it was\Njust something that was on TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.18,0:14:05.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't bother me!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.39,0:14:07.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No one needs to be concerned with such small details!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.31,0:14:07.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.86,0:14:13.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Therefore, she must be at the memorial hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.61,0:14:14.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can't be wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.65,0:14:15.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you think, Aya-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.78,0:14:20.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Jeez, Sonoko's deduction...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.95,0:14:24.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that old lady must have watched that drama.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.87,0:14:28.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Her coming to Beika should have\Nsomething to do with the drama.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.79,0:14:29.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But what is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.42,0:14:34.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, instead of just standing here listening to my\Ndeduction, why not go there and have a look?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.34,0:14:35.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.05,0:14:35.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.59,0:14:40.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just saw this woman you're looking for.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.55,0:14:43.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just as I thought, my deduction was correct!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.35,0:14:44.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is she still inside?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.93,0:14:45.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.93,0:14:48.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She must have left here 10 minutes ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.73,0:14:49.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She left?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.31,0:14:50.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could she be mistaken?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.06,0:14:54.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe she left because Aya-san wasn't here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.86,0:14:57.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, how did she look then?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.36,0:15:01.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When she came here, she kept looking\Nat the windows on the second floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.28,0:15:05.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Afterward, she asked if she could go in, so I said she could.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.33,0:15:09.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It didn't seem like she came to rescue Aya-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.25,0:15:10.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.75,0:15:13.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seeing as she just went back ten minutes ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.34,0:15:15.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She should still be somewhere around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.38,0:15:16.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you know where she went?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.13,0:15:18.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, she went over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.68,0:15:20.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll look for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.14,0:15:21.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, we'll come along too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.64,0:15:25.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And how did she look when she left?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.10,0:15:29.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She looked like she couldn't believe what she was seeing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.77,0:15:32.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I tried speaking to her, she\Ndidn't respond and just left like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.82,0:15:33.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.11,0:15:37.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait a second...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.70,0:15:40.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perhaps something inside is the key to this mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.95,0:15:43.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,May I come in?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.41,0:15:44.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please do.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.05,0:16:03.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.22,0:16:05.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The old Beika Hospital?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.93,0:16:10.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Particularly any of Mozart's works.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.31,0:16:12.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.87,0:16:27.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ayako...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.91,0:16:29.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.04,0:16:30.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mom is coming to you...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.92,0:16:36.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.84,0:16:41.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Lady!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.14,0:16:46.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.94,0:16:54.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe Fumie-san is on her way home.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.44,0:16:55.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.40,0:16:58.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's Shinichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.82,0:17:00.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.53,0:17:02.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran, I saw your message.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.03,0:17:02.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where are you right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.90,0:17:05.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In front of the Shitara Memorial Hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.12,0:17:08.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ask the woman to play something by Mozart right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.24,0:17:09.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mozart?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.45,0:17:10.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.50,0:17:11.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll go.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.75,0:17:13.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sonoko is going now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.04,0:17:14.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can I speak with Aya san?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.71,0:17:16.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shinichi wants to talk to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.00,0:17:17.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.29,0:17:19.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hello, this is Aya.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.80,0:17:20.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aya-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.92,0:17:24.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fumie-san is at the old Beika Hospital right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.68,0:17:25.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Beika Hospital?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.68,0:17:27.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.05,0:17:29.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fumie-san is going to commit suicide\Nin order to be with her daughter!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.52,0:17:38.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You have to make it, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.71,0:18:03.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aya-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.72,0:18:07.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fumie-san's daughter was once a\Npatient at the old Beika Hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.22,0:18:09.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She likely stayed in one of the rooms on the second floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.85,0:18:14.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The sound of Mozart's piano pieces\Ncoming from the Shitara residence...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.43,0:18:16.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would bring comfort to her daughter's spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.90,0:18:20.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From the window in that patient room,\Nshe could see the Shitara residence.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.40,0:18:22.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was what Fumie-san saw on the TV drama.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.78,0:18:28.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was so surprised that she couldn't sit still...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.62,0:18:29.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And immediately left for Beika.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.53,0:18:35.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Afterward, from the windows of the Shitara\NMemorial Hall, she could see the old Beika Hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.87,0:18:39.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She probably couldn't believe what she saw...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.88,0:18:43.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That building had remained intact for the last forty years.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.84,0:18:44.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This way!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.72,0:18:47.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fumie-san left for the hospital from there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.38,0:18:51.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, the moment she stopped in\Nfront of the old hospital building...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.01,0:18:54.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Unforgettable memories came rushing back.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.02,0:18:58.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fumie-san always held herself\Nresponsible for her daughter's death...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.52,0:18:59.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And now...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.35,0:19:01.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's planning to go be with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.36,0:19:05.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only one who can stop her, Aya san...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.49,0:19:06.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.09,0:19:08.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.58,0:19:14.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Grandma!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.08,0:19:22.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ayako...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.34,0:19:25.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only one who an stop her Aya-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.71,0:19:26.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.72,0:19:30.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mom...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.80,0:19:33.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've only been alive for 17 years, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.60,0:19:34.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I feel very lucky...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.02,0:19:38.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To be my mother's daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.23,0:19:40.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really lucky.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.65,0:19:42.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've always wanted to tell you that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.11,0:19:44.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ayako...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.69,0:19:47.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why you have to keep on living, Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.44,0:19:49.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Live my life through yours, all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.20,0:19:53.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I will...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.28,0:19:55.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I will, Ayako.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.12,0:19:56.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.25,0:20:00.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Grandma?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.79,0:20:02.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aya-chan...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.08,0:20:04.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Grandma...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.50,0:20:08.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just then, Ayako came here...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.34,0:20:09.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That child...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.13,0:20:10.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.84,0:20:12.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Forgave me...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.34,0:20:15.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's great, Grandma...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.10,0:20:17.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's great...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.43,0:20:19.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.52,0:20:21.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You found her!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.15,0:20:27.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shinichi-kun...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.53,0:20:31.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess I fulfilled the promise we made four years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.45,0:20:32.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.53,0:20:34.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like I did, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.16,0:20:37.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're pretty good at soccer.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.33,0:20:39.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you going to be a professional soccer player someday?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.08,0:20:39.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.75,0:20:40.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I want to be a detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.66,0:20:41.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.66,0:20:43.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like Holmes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.46,0:20:45.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sherlock Holmes?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.21,0:20:47.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before I do that, I'll first become a high school detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.80,0:20:49.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And not just a kid playing around.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.42,0:20:51.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A real detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.34,0:20:54.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How about we make a deal, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.97,0:20:56.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The next time we meet...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.51,0:20:58.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, four or five years from now...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.76,0:21:00.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I will become a real actress...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.10,0:21:03.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And you will become a real detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.65,0:21:06.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.61,0:21:07.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.73,0:21:08.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And as I was saying...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.94,0:21:10.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm impressed you could solve it with just a message.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.57,0:21:11.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.74,0:21:14.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just a matter of applying the formula of\Ndeduction to the equation of the mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.91,0:21:17.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Later, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.99,0:21:19.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Later.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.20,0:21:23.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran-neechan!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.00,0:21:25.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.33,0:21:27.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is everyone over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.13,0:21:28.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, and you found the old lady, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.30,0:21:31.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And what are you doing over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.34,0:21:35.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't get across, can you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.30,0:21:37.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's hilarious!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.18,0:21:39.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why you...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.89,0:21:41.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran-san, Sonoko-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.39,0:21:42.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.68,0:21:44.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan-kun, thank you, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.35,0:21:46.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm glad!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.40,0:21:48.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's go home now, Grandma.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.61,0:21:50.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.64,0:21:52.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come back when you have time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.53,0:21:54.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.07,0:21:56.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.03,0:21:57.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bye-bye!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.87,0:21:59.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bye-bye!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.53,0:22:02.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That really was some acting.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.66,0:23:31.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the end, the case had a happy ending.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.50,0:23:33.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, from that day onward...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.71,0:23:37.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, here she goes again...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.80,0:23:39.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That promise you made 4 years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.93,0:23:41.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was it, Shinichi!?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.59,0:23:45.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like I won't be able to call her for a while...
